  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2020-09-29",
    "date": "2022-04-20T18:04:40Z",
    "text": "Informing Grandfamilies Act\n\nThis bill requires states to notify kinship caregivers (e.g., grandparents or other relatives caring for a minor child) about (1) the care and placement options under federal, state, and local laws, (2) the requirements to become a foster family home, (3) whether the state has elected to make guardianship assistance payments, and (4) other policies under the state program that may assist such caregivers."
